From 10b338ddfc55dd22090ff2993cb9fa49c292057b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: suharvest <suharvest@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 23:16:12 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/6] feat(qwen3-tts): port streaming worker (base, N>1
 slot-pool) onto v0.8.0

Bring the standalone Qwen3-TTS streaming worker from v071/customvoice-product
onto release/0.8.0, driving the BASE fixed-speaker path (no CustomVoice).

Runtime (qwen3OmniTTSRuntime.{h,cpp}):
- Add standalone-TTS streaming hooks to the existing non-streaming
  handleAudioGeneration/runTalkerGenerationLoop: 3-param StreamingChunkCallback,
  per-request codecChunkFrames/subsequentChunkFrames/onAudioChunkReady/shouldCancel,
  PerBatchTalkerState.lastChunkEnd, PerBatchStreamingHooks, and a defaulted
  streamingHooks loop param. Per-frame chunk emit + cancel poll inside the decode
  loop; remainder flush after. Empty hooks => identical non-streaming behavior.

Worker (examples/omni/qwen3_tts_streaming_worker.cpp, slotPool.h, CMakeLists):
- New qwen3_tts_streaming_worker target (JSON-line stdin/stdout, slot-pool).
- N>1 via independent runtime instances per slot (Option A). Shared-engine ctor
  DEFERRED (needs LLMEngineRunner::getEngine() not on 0.8.0) -> validate 8GB VRAM
  with tegrastats before raising --max_slots.
- Drop CustomVoice-only request fields (language/predictor*/codec_eos_logit_offset)
  and the StatefulCode2WavRunner dependency (slot-pool uses per-slot stateless
  Code2Wav). Build with ENABLE_CUTE_DSL=OFF on JetPack CUDA 12.6.

NOT yet build-verified on Orin (authored on Mac; arch-specific build pending).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

